# comments.iron expected-scopes reference.
Token                    | Scope
-------------------------|--------------------------------
// plain line comment    | comment.line.double-slash.iron
/* block comment */      | comment.block.iron
/// doc comment          | comment.block.documentation.iron

Covers UI-SPEC S6 all three comment forms. The doc-comment scope
comment.block.documentation.iron is the theme-distinction win called
out in CONTEXT D-02 specifics — themes surface /// distinctly from //.

Note: grammar ordering in iron.tmLanguage.json places doc-comments BEFORE
line-comments so /// matches first (otherwise // would swallow the /// as
a plain line comment).
